b?topicID=202.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/artemis3.bmp></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> * The Goddess Artemis appears over Themiscrya, standing on a mountain peak, her hands clasped together, she smiled watching the land and the Amazons busy themselves in there village. The winter was harsh, very harsh for the Amazons and for the animals, many have migrated out of the lands for fear of hypothermia and frostbite...she closes her eyes*<br>
<br>
I say a blessing for the Amazons, there hunts will be plentifull this season, there will be an abundance of wild game, more so then usual to make up for cruleness of the winter.<br>
<br>
*Artemis then forms a green light in her hands, she throws it out into the forest, the forest illuminates for a while then the light dies, Artemis smiles, her work here be done * <p>Goddess Artemis
Protector of the Amazons
Goddess of the Moon and the Hunt</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazondelerium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon DeLerium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#993300>(5/6/01 9:14:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/amazondelerium?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> ~ DeL walked down a path she used often when wanting to be alone in the woods, suddenly , everything felt odd, as if someone was pressing on the air, then it all turned green. DeL jumped up grabbing onto a tree branch, she then hoisted herself up, branch by branch until she was almost at the top of the tree, sitting up on a branch she parted some leaves and looked out upon forest, she caught a glimps of a lone figure atop a closeby mountain, she recognized Artemis' figure, and the way she held herself. ~<br>
<br>
~Suddenly, everything went back to normal and Artemis vanished, DeL began to make her way down, feeling blessed that she was able to catch a glimps of the Hunt GOddess, as she neared the lowest branches, she noticed a few more deer and rabbits then what was usual for this time of the season, she smiled~<br>
<br>
Thank You Great Goddess Artemis....<br>
<br>
~she got up, standing on the branch and flipped down to the ground, she decided to walk to the meadow for some well needed meditation time.~ <p>~*Amazon DeLerium*~
~*RoC Princess for SoT*~
~~* DeL *~~

Pain is just weakness
Leaving the Body</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#993300>(5/6/01 11:52:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> Alysia appeared standing behind Artemis on that mountain peak. She smiled hearing the Goddess give a blessing. <br>
<br>
&quot;I myself would do something similar, but I have chosen to give up my Goddess title.&quot; She smiled at the thought.<br>
<br>
She then looked down into the village of Themiscrya where she had planted an evergrowing tree that would never perish and always bear pleantiful fruit. It was indeed surrounded by a flame that could only be touched by an amazon.<br>
<br>
&quot;I however, have left my mark I think. As well as my blessing.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#993300>(5/23/01 9:01:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/artemis3.bmp></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> ~turns her head and looks at the little girl~<br>
Do you mind...Im having a moment... <p>Goddess Artemis
Protector of the Amazons
~*~Goddess of the hunt and the Moon~*~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#993300>(6/1/01 4:23:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> ::Poseidon appears at Artemis' side invisible to all mortals. He shakes his head as if sad and grieved.::<br>
<br>
&quot;All those poor amazons. Suffering and nothing the gods could have done. A pity that the ones they worship have no power to help them in their times of distress. But then I hear Zeus wished it so&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#993300>(6/1/01 6:49:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> ::Sar sits on a ledge just below the mountain peak. She listens silently to the conversations, but never spoke her own words. In her own mind she thanked the goddess for supplyingher athelfi with a bountiful hunt for the season. It would raise spirits once again. She chuckled lightly to herself and stood up to get a better look at the stunning scenery that made home to the Amazons:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/01 11:28:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/artemis3.bmp></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> * looks to Poseidon and shakes her head *<br>
I do not go against Zeus' ruling, he knows whats best...besides, the Amazons are strong....suviving this winter proved that. * smiles proudly * They didnt need the help of the Gods to do it. You cant say that for most other mortals... <p>Goddess Artemis
Protector of the Amazons
~*~Goddess of the hunt and the Moon~*~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/01 11:32:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/artemis3.bmp></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> * smiles seeing Sartha, she walks over to her * Beautiful veiw, isnt it. * Takes the pin from her hair setting her auburn locks free to blow in the breeze * Themiscrya is one of my favorite lands to visit. It is the most beautiful, and the oldest. <p>Goddess Artemis
Protector of the Amazons
~*~Goddess of the hunt and the Moon~*~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/01 3:13:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> ::those silvery-golden orbs glance to the great goddess and she smiles lightly, nodding. She then turns her gaze back to the land::<br>
<br>
&quot;It's gorgeous... This is the land I call my home, and I am proud beyond my own life.&quot;<br>
<br>
::She closed her eyes for a moment as they breeze allows her soul to roam. These were the best kinds of moment::<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you for your blessings, Artemis... The Amazon will always be your allies...&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/01 7:39:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=pos006 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> ::The god Poseidon gazes at Artemis as she walks away. He smiles knowing his gift would surely win the hearts of the amazons. He then vanishes in a flash of blue light.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#993300>(6/4/01 11:14:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/artemis3.bmp></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: * Standing upon a mountain peak *</span><hr size=1> * Smiles to Sartha *<br>
The land is your as you belong to the land. You being one of the older Amazons know this. The essance of the Ancient Amazons live on inside of you, and your sisters, as well as the land. For ages Amazons have lived in Themiscrya.<br>
It pleases to me to no end to see how long this tribe has thrived, much longer then most of the other tribes. But in all respect, they too were great tribes.<br>
<br>
I will always help my Amazons. I know they will always be my allies, tho , they do have the right to worship others, and I repect that. However, those who turn on me to my uncle, well, I hope they can survive with a horid hunt. I will never help them....I too can be petty as all the Goddesses and Gods can be. I dont want to be, but will be...<br>
<br>
But noone should worry about that. I have faith in all the Amazons.... <p>Goddess Artemis
Protector of the Amazons
~*~Goddess of the hunt and the Moon~*~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#993300>(6/4/01 3:22:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::smiles lightly::</span><hr size=1> ::nods and smiles that strangely cold smile of hers that never quite touched her eyes. It was the most Sartha could ever offer a person, but in times like this she wished there was more::<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, every tribe was a great asset to our Nation, past and present. None shall be forgotten, and you shall not be forsaken, dear Goddess. My athelfi have thought of themselves as your &quot;daughters&quot; in the hunt and life for so long. We know better than to leave you for the petty promises of a god like Poseidon. Our loyalties will not change because of one spring, when you have given us the sources to survive even in the harshest of times. Poseidon seeks us out for his own gain, this we know, but you simple stay with us through it all without question... You are truly an Amazon to us. Poseidon could never be one of us...&quot;<br>
<br>
::with that she sighs and looks back out at the land:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=daphnikearephiparthenia>Daphnike Arephi Parthenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(7/5/01 12:09:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hunt return</span><hr size=1> * Daphnike goes up the peak after a great hunt, where the young Amazon killed a deer, to honor the Goddess Artemis.*<br>
<br>
Oh!Kalos Theosissa, thanks for blessing the lands of Themiskyra, ephkharisto!I never saw a hunting season so great, it'll change us of the winter's harshness.Thanks for that abundance, thanks for helping us, thanks for giving birth to our Nation. The Amazon Nation could never be enough thankful for all your graces! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#993300>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#993300> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya>Sisters of Themiscrya</a> <font color=#993300> - </font><a href="http://www.amazonsunite.i-p.com">Home</a><font color=#993300> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.3 b4<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  